FBIS3-15983 "drsov048_u_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 Latvia Minister Signs Protocol for German Assistance LD1003220294 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1800 GMT 10 Mar 94 LD1003220294 Riga Radio Riga Network Language: Latvian Article Type:BFN [Text] Today in Riga, Girts Kristovskis, Latvian minister of internal affairs, and Reinhard Teiling, a spokesman for the German Ministry of Internal Affairs, signed a protocol to the treaty concluded in 1992 between the two Ministries of Internal Affairs on technical assistance to the latvian Ministry of Internal Affairs. A news conference was held after the signing of the protocol. Linards Mucins, parliamentary secretary at the Latvian Ministry of Internal Affairs, said that this treaty provides for German assistance to a value of 3 million marks to the internal affairs system of Latvia. Most of this sum is due to be used for acquiring communications equipment. At present a new cooperation treaty with the German Ministry of Internal Affairs is in preparation.
